Text.Value: I shall bring her Sharess' wisdom and she will provide catnip for our ecstatic visions!
Yes - I pledge myself to Sharess.
Now - will you heed our Mother's call, and bolster her as she crushes the heathen Absolute beneath her divine paw?
*Mew. Meeew!*
You have delivered unto me a most studious disciple - when you next hear thunder, know it is Sharess herself purring her approval.
Who? Speak their name and I shall bring them the full force of Sharess' soporific glory!
*Mew? Meow. Rrrrrr!*
Actually never mind - it's better if you focus your priestly attentions here.
*HISS!*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Please reuse CAT_Rig_CINE_Aggresive_Idle_01 for the hiss and HUM_M_Rig_SCENE_SHA_SoftShooingAway_PLYR for the Player shooing the cat. <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: It is as you say - I shall sing the hymns of Sharess to the stars as she intended!
May your dusks be long and your hunger fleeting.
Try and scare the cat away.
Well, you're an excitable little thing.
Leave.
Mother of Cats! Feline of Felicity! The only deity one should ever swear fealty to in these nine lives!
*Purrrrrrrrrr.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Animation of PLYR petting the cat. [Gwen Lee]

Text.Value: Yes. Yes, I have.
Who's Sharess?
Yes and no. Your kind has lost their way in their worship of the Feline of Felicity - you only hold to her basest tenets.
Yes? Will you now heed the most splendid Sharess' call?
From one follower of a deity to another, I must respectfully decline.
I know someone who'd truly appreciate Sharess' guidance in her time of need.
*Meooow!*
Do you want to be my friend, puss?
I know somebody who needs to hear Sharess' word straight from the mouth of her most loyal priest.
Derryth Bonecloak - she's just lost someone and could use some solace.
Ah, a fellow priest. You may walk on two legs, but we still see eye to eye.
Attempt to pet the cat.
Leave.
Leave.
Leave.
Hold, seeker! Have you come to swear yourself to Sharess by my paw?
I'm not sure Sharess is the goddess for me.
*Meoooow! Mrah.*
Sharess shall mourn your absence - but always honour your capriciousness as her own.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little disheartened but respectful of the player's choice

Text.Value: If you want more of that, you should befriend Derryth Bonecloak back there.
The apothecary? But of course! Sharess has sent me a fine new disciple and purveyor of the sacred herb!
I will sing her name in the streets, and you will bring her prayers to those suffering two legs instead of four.
*Meow! Meow!*
Yes! Yes! Together we shall spread the word of the wonder in her every pawstep!
*Hiss!*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Please reuse CAT_Rig_CINE_Aggresive_Idle_01 for the hiss. <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: Praise Sharess!
*Rrrrrrr?*
Uh, yes. I will definitely do that.
Sharess as in Sharess' Caress?

Synopsis: A cat you can send over to Derryth Bonecloak if Baelen is dead. It speaks in rolled r's and is very difficult to understand.
